</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF35FC5A7F47B0F1" blockId="10.[219,607,906,955]" box="[219,607,906,928]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">M a t e r i a l e x a m i n e d. Two workers:</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="21E86513FFF85F5CFF35FC757FB4B6FA" pageId="10" pageNumber="405" type="description">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF35FC757CE7B0EA" blockId="10.[219,607,906,955]" box="[219,511,933,955]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">1) Baltic amber, CGC F-6800.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF35FC0C7956B746" blockId="10.[166,1225,988,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">Measurements (in mm): HL 0.69, HW 0.60, FW 0.27, FLW 0.31, SL 0.46, ML 0.75, PnW 0.75, PL 0.31, PW 0.23, PPL 0.21, PPW 0.30, ESD 0.27, total length ca. 3.0.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF35FBCC7C9CB706" blockId="10.[166,1225,988,1111]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">Indices: HL/HW 1.15, FW/HW 0.45, FLW/FW 1.15, SL/HL 0.67, SL/HW 0.77, PL/HL 0.45, PPL/HL 0.30.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF35FBAA7957B7C1" blockId="10.[219,1103,1146,1168]" box="[219,1103,1146,1168]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
2) 
<collectingRegion id="AB36F87AFFF85F5CFF1AFBAA7C2CB7C1" box="[244,308,1146,1168]" country="Ukraine" name="Rivne" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">Rovno</collectingRegion>
amber, SIZK K-7026 (specimen damaged, without petiole, postpetiole and gaster).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF35FB677C57B643" blockId="10.[166,1225,1207,1362]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">Measurements (in mm): HL 0.66, HW 0.57, SL 0.52, FW 0.23, FLW 0.26, AL 0.85, PnW 0.39, ESL 0.31, ESD 0.30, HTL 0.52, total length ca. 3.5 (by analogy of ML+HL compare to other species).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF35FAC77CA3B603" blockId="10.[166,1225,1207,1362]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">Indices: HL/HW 1.16, SL/HL 0.79, SL/HW 0.91, FW/HW 0.46, FLW/FW 1.13, ESL/ HL 0.47, ESL/HW 0.53.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF48FA457FB4B6FA" blockId="10.[166,684,1429,1451]" box="[166,684,1429,1451]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF85F5CFF48FA457FB4B6FA" bold="true" box="[166,684,1429,1451]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
A key for the identification of 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFF85F5CFE3DFA457FB4B6FA" box="[467,684,1429,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF85F5CFE3DFA457F79B6FB" bold="true" box="[467,609,1429,1450]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">Eocenomyrma</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="21E86513FFF85F5DFF48FA1E79D5B150" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="406" pageId="10" pageNumber="405" type="key">
<key id="1D6361A9FFF85F5DFF48FA1E79D5B150" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="406" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<keyStep id="D2062E3DFFF85F5CFF48FA1E79D1B5FF" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF48FA1E79D1B509" blockId="10.[166,1225,1486,1854]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<keyLead id="D20395ADFFF85F5CFF48FA1E79D1B509" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
1. Head, mesosoma and waist only densely punctated, without rugosity or reticulation (
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFBF0FA1E7948B6B5" box="[1054,1104,1486,1508]" captionStart="Figs 7–8" captionStartId="6.[170,209,1082,1104]" captionTargetBox="[189,1190,179,1041]" captionTargetId="figure-259@6.[128,1262,171,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 7–8. Eocenomyrma breviscapa sp. n., photos of holotype worker: 7 — body in dorsal view; 8 — body in lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449292/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Scape relatively very short, SL/HL 0.52, SL/HW 0.57. Petiole with very short peduncle, PL/ 
<collectingCountry id="11E57608FFF85F5CFBEAFA3B793BB550" box="[1028,1059,1515,1537]" name="Philippines" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">PH</collectingCountry>
1.13, its anterior surface steep, very slightly concave, meets with dorsal surface of node at an acute angle, dorsal plate short ant strongly declined posteriorly so that petiole seems cuneiform (seen in profile) (
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFBAFF9F5796EB56A" box="[1089,1142,1573,1595]" captionStart="Figs 7–8" captionStartId="6.[170,209,1082,1104]" captionTargetBox="[189,1190,179,1041]" captionTargetId="figure-259@6.[128,1262,171,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 7–8. Eocenomyrma breviscapa sp. n., photos of holotype worker: 7 — body in dorsal view; 8 — body in lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449292" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449292/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">figs 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFB91F9F57981B56A" box="[1151,1177,1573,1595]" captionStart="Figs 9–11" captionStartId="7.[174,213,1774,1796]" captionTargetBox="[212,1219,370,1696]" captionTargetId="figure-11@7.[182,1223,341,1715]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 9–11. Eocenomyrma breviscapa sp. n., line drawings of holotype worker made based on photos: 9 — body in dorsal view; 10 — body in lateral view; 11 — head in dorsal view (sculpture omitted). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449294" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449294/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">10</figureCitation>
). ..... ................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFF85F5CFBE0F9927988B506" authority="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky, 2016" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky" authorityYear="2016" box="[1038,1168,1602,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapa" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF85F5CFBE0F9927988B506" box="[1038,1168,1602,1623]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">E. breviscapa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="40B557F1FFF85F5CFB78F99279D1B509" box="[1174,1225,1602,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF48F98E79D1B5FF" blockId="10.[166,1225,1486,1854]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<keyLead id="D20395ADFFF85F5CFF48F98E79D1B5FF" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
– Head, mesosoma and waist longitudinally rugose or reticulated; petiole of another shape, but in any case with much longer peduncle, PL/ 
<collectingCountry id="11E57608FFF85F5CFDB8F9AB7F6DB5C0" box="[598,629,1659,1681]" name="Philippines" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">PH</collectingCountry>
&gt; 1.25 (
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFD2FF9AB7FEFB5C0" box="[705,759,1659,1681]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[576,609,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[576,1224,678,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-353@4.[573,1227,655,1759]" captionText="Fig. 5. Eocenomyrma ukrainica sp. n., photo of paratype gyne, body in lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6462410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6462410/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFCEEF9AB7E15B5C0" box="[768,781,1659,1681]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[174,719,767,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-475@5.[174,719,767,1738]" captionText="Fig. 6. Eocenomyrma ukrainica sp. n., line drawing of paratype gyne made based on photo, body in lateral view (sculpture omitted). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6462414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6462414/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">6</figureCitation>
, 12–17) Scape distinctly longer, SL/HL&gt; 0.58, SL/HW&gt; 0.70. ..................................................................................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="D2062E3DFFF85F5CFF48F96579D1B46F" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF48F96579D1B455" blockId="10.[166,1225,1486,1854]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<keyLead id="D20395ADFFF85F5CFF48F96579D1B455" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
2(1). Gyne: propodeal spines relatively short (ESL/HL 0.17), straight, slightly widened at the base; head dorsum and mesosoma mostly longitudinally rugose, coarse reticulation presents on occipital area of the head (
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFEC2F93E7C79B455" box="[300,353,1774,1796]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[576,609,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[576,1224,678,1756]" captionTargetId="figure-353@4.[573,1227,655,1759]" captionText="Fig. 5. Eocenomyrma ukrainica sp. n., photo of paratype gyne, body in lateral view. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6462410" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6462410/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFE85F93E7C61B455" box="[363,377,1774,1796]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[174,207,1755,1777]" captionTargetBox="[174,719,767,1738]" captionTargetId="figure-475@5.[174,719,767,1738]" captionText="Fig. 6. Eocenomyrma ukrainica sp. n., line drawing of paratype gyne made based on photo, body in lateral view (sculpture omitted). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6462414" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6462414/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">6</figureCitation>
). ...................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFF85F5CFBF2F93F7988B452" authority="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky, 2016" authorityName="Radchenko &amp; Dlussky" authorityYear="2016" box="[1052,1168,1774,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ukrainica" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF85F5CFBF2F93F7988B452" box="[1052,1168,1774,1796]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">E. ukrainica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="40B557F1FFF85F5CFB78F93E79D1B455" box="[1174,1225,1774,1796]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF85F5CFF48F8DB79D1B46F" blockId="10.[166,1225,1486,1854]" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
<keyLead id="D20395ADFFF85F5CFF48F8DB79D1B46F" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">
– Workers: propodeal spines longer (ESL/HL&gt; 0.23), more widened at the base, often curved down along their length, if straight, then much longer, ESL/HL&gt; 0.35 (
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF85F5CFCCDF8F87E92B46F" box="[803,906,1832,1854]" captionStart-0="Figs 12–13" captionStart-1="Figs 14–17" captionStartId-0="8.[170,209,1758,1780]" captionStartId-1="9.[172,211,1762,1784]" captionTargetBox-0="[220,1213,213,1708]" captionTargetBox-1="[217,1181,429,1704]" captionTargetId-0="figure-12@8.[156,1227,171,1726]" captionTargetId-1="figure-69@9.[195,1212,398,1724]" captionTargetPageId-0="8" captionTargetPageId-1="9" captionText-0="Figs 12–13. Line drawings of Eocenomyrma rugosostriata (Mayr), neotype worker (12, body in dorso-lateral view) and E. elegantula Dlussky et Radchenko, holotype worker (13, body in lateral view). Scale bar 1 mm." captionText-1="Figs 14–17. Line drawings of Eocenomyrma orthospina Dlussky et Radchenko, holotype worker (14 — head, mesosoma and waist, dorso-lateral view; 15 — mesosoma and petiole, lateral view) and E. eocenica Dlussky et Radchenko,holotype worker (16 — head,mesosoma and waist, dorso-lateral view; 17 — mesosoma and petiole, lateral view). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449296" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449299" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6449296/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6449299/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="405">figs 12–17</figureCitation>
). .................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="D2062E3DFFF95F5DFF45FF7F79D5B3AF" pageId="11" pageNumber="406">
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF95F5DFF45FF7F79D5B3B0" blockId="11.[171,1229,175,513]" pageId="11" pageNumber="406">
<keyLead id="D20395ADFFF95F5DFF45FF7F79D5B3B0" pageId="11" pageNumber="406">
3(2). Head dorsum and mesosoma with longitudinal, slightly sinuous rugosity, without reticulation (
<figureCitation id="F1C92A1DFFF95F5DFB66FF7F79DDB394" box="[1160,1221,175,197]" captionStart="Figs 12–13" captionStartId="8.[170,209,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[220,1213,213,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[156,1227,171,1726]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs 12–13. Line drawings of Eocenomyrma rugosostriata (Mayr), neotype worker (12, body in dorso-lateral view) and E. elegantula Dlussky et Radchenko, holotype worker (13, body in lateral view). Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449296/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="406">fig. 12</figureCitation>
) ......................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="AEF24D1BFFF95F5DFC00FF1C79D5B3B0" authority="(Mayr)" baseAuthorityName="Mayr" baseAuthorityYear="1868" box="[1006,1229,203,225]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Eocenomyrma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="406" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosostriata">
<emphasis id="5B86EA8AFFF95F5DFC00FF1C799BB3B0" box="[1006,1155,204,225]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="406">E. rugosostriata</emphasis>
(Mayr)
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="694D3698FFF95F5DFF45FF3879D5B3AF" blockId="11.[171,1229,175,513]" box="[171,1229,232,254]" pageId="11" pageNumber="406">
<keyLead id="D20395ADFFF95F5DFF45FF3879D5B3AF" box="[171,1229,232,254]" pageId="11" pageNumber="406">
– Head dorsum and mesosoma at least partly with reticulation (
